name: CoinWarmStart
brief: Abstract base class for warm start information.
detailed:
Provides the interface for warm start objects that store solver state enabling faster re-optimization. Derived classes implement solver-specific storage (e.g., variable/constraint basis status for simplex methods).
The class supports a diff mechanism for efficient incremental updates:generateDiff() computes changes from another warm startapplyDiff() applies a diff to update this warm start

methods.name: ~CoinWarmStart
methods.brief: Virtual destructor for proper cleanup of derived classes.

methods.name: clone
methods.brief: Create a deep copy of this warm start object.
methods.return_desc: Pointer to newly allocated copy (caller owns memory)

methods.name: generateDiff
methods.brief: Generate a diff representing changes from another warm start.
methods.detailed: Computes the difference between this warm start and another, enabling efficient storage of incremental changes.
methods.return_desc: Pointer to diff object (caller owns memory), or nullptr if not supported

parameters.name: oldWarmStart
parameters.description: The baseline warm start to compare against

methods.name: applyDiff
methods.brief: Apply a diff to update this warm start.
methods.detailed: Modifies this warm start by applying changes encoded in the diff object.
